
[1]smartness

   SM'ARTNESS, n.

   1. The quality of being smart or pungent; poignancy; as the smartness
   of pain.

   2. Quickness; vigor; as the smartness of a blow.

   3. Liveliness; briskness; vivacity; wittiness; as the smartness of a
   reply or of a phrase.
